      "content": "Libertarians like Ayn Rand and Murray Rothbard argue that government regulation of the internet infringes upon individuals' rights to free speech and property. The concept of \"nozickian\" entitlement, as outlined by Robert Nozick, suggests that individuals have a right to their own speech and ideas, which should be protected from government seizure or restriction. Additionally, the idea of \"property rights\" in information, as proposed by philosopher and computer scientist Edward S. Cornish, holds that individuals have a right to control and profit from their own ideas and creations.",
