      "content": "those are great. i want to frame the argument that any gov intervention, even for things like \"misinformation\" or \"safety\", is just a slippery slope to state-controlled truth. do you think there's a way to argue that these regulations are fundamentally illegitimate rather than just \"imperfect\"?",
